  "text": "The SpiderMonkey JIT compilation pipeline in Firefox is defined across five key C++ files in the js/src/jit/ directory of the mozilla-firefox/firefox codebase (github.com/sg-evals/firefox--871325b8):\n\n1. **Ion.cpp** defines the top-level IonCompile function (line 1765) which orchestrates the Ion optimizing compiler. This static function is the entry point that manages the overall compilation workflow, accepting a JSContext, script, and optional OSR (On-Stack Replacement) bytecode pointer.\n\n2. **IonCompileTask.h and IonCompileTask.cpp** define and implement the IonCompileTask class (header line 27), which represents a single off-thread Ion compilation task. This class extends HelperThreadTask and mozilla::LinkedListElement, managing the compilation of a script asynchronously on helper threads. The constructor is defined in IonCompileTask.cpp at line 63.\n\n3. **BaselineJIT.h and BaselineJIT.cpp** define and implement the BaselineScript class (header line 189), representing the first-tier JIT compiler that provides a native code representation. BaselineScript is an aligned final class that stores compiled code and metadata for baseline-compiled scripts, including offsets for warm-up checks and profiler instrumentation.\n\n4. **JitRuntime.h** defines the JitRuntime class (line 121), which manages per-runtime JIT state and infrastructure. This class is central to the JIT system, coordinating trampoline code, fallback handlers, and other runtime-specific JIT machinery.\n\n5. **JitOptions.h and JitOptions.cpp** define and implement JIT configuration through the DefaultJitOptions struct (header line 46), which encapsulates all configurable JIT compiler options. The global JitOptions instance is initialized at line 22 of JitOptions.cpp, with configuration defaults set in the constructor at line 62.\n\nThese components form the hierarchical JIT compilation pipeline: JitOptions provides configuration, JitRuntime provides per-runtime infrastructure, BaselineScript represents the first compilation tier, IonCompileTask manages off-thread compilation, and IonCompile orchestrates the entire Ion optimization process."
}

